olive oil
1 courgette
½ onion
1 parsnip
2 potato
40 g butter
2.5 tbs milk
¼ tsp salt
1 packet pork loin steaks
½ packet Homestyle Gravy

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Bring a medium saucepan of salted water to the boil. Thinly slice the courgette (unpeeled) into batons. Slice the red onion (see ingredients) into 2cm wedges. Slice the parsnip (unpeeled) into 1cm batons.
TIP: Cut the veggies to size so they cook in time.

Place the courgette, onion and parsnip on an oven tray lined with baking paper. Drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer and roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.
TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

While the veggies are roasting, peel the potato and cut into 2cm chunks. Cook the potato in the boiling water until easily pierced with a knife, 10-15 minutes. Drain and return the potato to the saucepan. Add the butter, milk and the salt and mash with a potato masher or fork until smooth. Cover to keep warm.

While the potato is cooking, heat a drizzle of olive oil in a large frying pan over a medium-high heat. When the oil is hot, cook the pork loin steaks until cooked through, 3-4 minutes each side (depending on thickness). Transfer to a plate and set aside to rest.
TIP: Pork can be served slightly blushing pink in the centre.

While the pork is resting, return the frying pan to a medium heat. Cook the homestyle gravy (see ingredients), stirring, until warmed through, 5 minutes.

Slice the seared pork. Divide the roasted veggies, mash and pork between plates. Spoon over the homestyle gravy.